            "https://example.com", _testContext.CancellationToken);

        Assert.IsTrue(response.IsSuccessStatusCode);
    }
}
```

Tip

MSTest analyzer rule [MSTEST0049](mstest-analyzers/mstest0049) helps identify async calls where `TestContext.CancellationToken` should be passed. It also provides a code fixer to apply the change automatically.

The following analyzers help ensure proper usage of the `TestContext` class:

*   [MSTEST0005](mstest-analyzers/mstest0005) - TestContext property should have valid layout.
*   [MSTEST0024](mstest-analyzers/mstest0024) - Do not store TestContext in a static member.
*   [MSTEST0033](mstest-analyzers/mstest0033) - Suppresses CS8618 for TestContext property.
*   [MSTEST0048](mstest-analyzers/mstest0048) - Avoid TestContext properties in fixture methods.
*   [MSTEST0049](mstest-analyzers/mstest0049) - Flow TestContext CancellationToken.
*   [MSTEST0054](mstest-analyzers/mstest0054) - Use CancellationToken property.

