Here's the complete migration plan for your project. I found **7 breaking changes** that need attention:

---

### 1. Project File → MSTest.Sdk
Replace the SDK and remove all MSTest package references:
```xml
<!-- Before -->
<Project Sdk="Microsoft.NET.Sdk">
  <PropertyGroup>
    <TargetFramework>net6.0</TargetFramework>
    <IsPackable>false</IsPackable>
  </PropertyGroup>
  <ItemGroup>
    <PackageReference Include="MSTest.TestFramework" Version="3.8.0" />
    <PackageReference Include="MSTest.TestAdapter" Version="3.8.0" />
    <PackageReference Include="Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk" Version="17.13.0" />
  </ItemGroup>
</Project>

<!-- After -->
<Project Sdk="MSTest.Sdk/4.1.0">
  <PropertyGroup>
    <TargetFramework>net8.0</TargetFramework>
  </PropertyGroup>
</Project>
```
- **`net6.0` → `net8.0`**: .NET 6 support is dropped; `net8.0` is the minimum.
- **`IsPackable`** and all **PackageReferences** are handled by the SDK implicitly.

---

### 2. Custom TestMethodAttribute → `ExecuteAsync`
`Execute(ITestMethod)` is removed. Override `ExecuteAsync` instead, and propagate caller info attributes:
```csharp
// Before
public sealed class LoggingTestMethodAttribute : TestMethodAttribute
{
    public override TestResult[] Execute(ITestMethod testMethod) { ... }
}

// After
public sealed class LoggingTestMethodAttribute : TestMethodAttribute
{
    public LoggingTestMethodAttribute(
        [CallerFilePath] string callerFilePath = "",
        [CallerLineNumber] int callerLineNumber = -1)
        : base(callerFilePath, callerLineNumber) { }

    public override Task<TestResult[]> ExecuteAsync(ITestMethod testMethod)
    {
        Console.WriteLine($"Starting: {testMethod.TestMethodName}");
        return base.ExecuteAsync(testMethod);
    }
}
```

---

### 3. `[ExpectedException]` → `Assert.ThrowsExactly`
The attribute is removed entirely:
```csharp
// Before
[ExpectedException(typeof(ArgumentException))]
[TestMethod]
public void Validate_BadInput_Throws()
{
    throw new ArgumentException("bad");
}

// After
[TestMethod]
public void Validate_BadInput_Throws()
{
    Assert.ThrowsExactly<ArgumentException>(() => throw new ArgumentException("bad"));
}
```

---

### 4. `ClassCleanupBehavior` enum removed
`EndOfClass` is now the only behavior. Remove the parameter:
```csharp
// Before
[ClassCleanup(ClassCleanupBehavior.EndOfClass)]

// After
[ClassCleanup]
```

---

### 5. `TestContext.Properties.Contains` → `.ContainsKey`
`Properties` changed from `IDictionary` to `IDictionary<string, object>`:
```csharp
// Before
TestContext.Properties.Contains("env");

// After
TestContext.Properties.ContainsKey("env");
```

---

### 6. `Assert.AreEqual` message format params removed
The `(expected, actual, message, params object[])` overload is gone. Use string interpolation:
```csharp
// Before
Assert.AreEqual(1, 1, "Expected {0}", 1);

// After
Assert.AreEqual(1, 1, $"Expected {1}");
```

---

### 7. `TestTimeout.Infinite` enum removed
Replace with `int.MaxValue`:
```csharp
// Before
[Timeout(TestTimeout.Infinite)]

// After
[Timeout(int.MaxValue)]
```

---

### Summary checklist

| # | Change | Scope |
|---|--------|-------|
| 1 | SDK → `MSTest.Sdk/4.1.0`, TFM → `net8.0` | `.csproj` |
| 2 | `Execute` → `ExecuteAsync` + caller-info ctor | `LoggingTestMethodAttribute` |
| 3 | `[ExpectedException]` → `Assert.ThrowsExactly` | `Validate_BadInput_Throws` |
| 4 | Remove `ClassCleanupBehavior.EndOfClass` param | `Cleanup` method |
| 5 | `.Contains` → `.ContainsKey` | `RunIntegration` |
| 6 | Message format params → string interpolation | `RunIntegration` |
| 7 | `TestTimeout.Infinite` → `int.MaxValue` | `LongRunning` |

All 7 items are sourced from the [official v3→v4 migration guide](https://learn.microsoft.com/dotnet/core/testing/unit-testing-mstest-migration-v3-v4). Want me to implement these changes?
